Abyss agents depends on following components:

- graphite server to store metrics 
- grafana dashboards for visualization 
- apache web server for http requestes  
- elasticsearch for storing dashboard. 

setup-graphite.sh script will set up all graphite, grafana, apache and ES services on a single server.

graphite carbon servers are configured to use port: 7405 7406,7407.
grafana is client side application (java script) that runs in the browser. grafana can save dashboards on 
any system running ES allowing ingress traffic to elasticsearch ports. 
elastic search (ES) is configured to use port: 7410 7411. 
apache server listens on standard http port: 80

To confirm the setup successful , run "$sudo netstat -ltpn". It should show python (carbon) processes, 
java (ES), and http (apache) are listening to correct ports. Make sure your systems have all these ingress ports open in firewall or security group.  
$sudo netstat -ltpn
Active Internet connections (only servers)
Proto Recv-Q Send-Q Local Address           Foreign Address         State       PID/Program name
tcp        0      0 0.0.0.0:22              0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      1040/sshd       
tcp        0      0 0.0.0.0:7405            0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      12573/python  << graphite carbon
tcp        0      0 0.0.0.0:7406            0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      12573/python  << graphite carbon
tcp        0      0 0.0.0.0:7407            0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      12573/python  << graphite carbon
...
tcp6       0      0 :::7410                 :::*                    LISTEN      12554/java     << ES    
tcp6       0      0 :::80                   :::*                    LISTEN      12382/apache2  << apache
tcp6       0      0 :::7411                 :::*                    LISTEN      12554/java     << ES    

